    <item>
      <title>Admin account</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/admin_account/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/admin_account/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;default-account&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Default account&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#default-account&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immediately after installation&lt;/strong&gt;, the first thing (for security reasons) is to change the data of the default account of the platform administrator.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Default data after installation: login &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:admin@admin.com&#34;&gt;admin@admin.com&lt;/a&gt; password: admin.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;And so, to replace the data with your own, go to the My Profile page by clicking on the icon next to the Name on the left in the site header.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_12-09-08.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Also, change the passwords or disable the accounts &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:manager@manager.com&#34;&gt;manager@manager.com&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:customer@customer.com&#34;&gt;customer@customer.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Overview</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/overview/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview-and-introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Overview and Introduction&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#overview-and-introduction&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technologies and frameworks used in the platform:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Laravel 8.1 for backend&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Angular 17 for frontend&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Ionic 8, Angular17+ and Capacitor for the mobile part&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The mobile part can also use Cordova plugins.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>SMTP settings</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/smtp/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/smtp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;smtp-settings&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  SMTP settings&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#smtp-settings&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The program uses email notifications during registration and password recovery.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Enter your details. You can obtain this information from your provider.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-03-30.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Domain settings</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/domain/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/domain/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;domain-settings&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Domain settings&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#domain-settings&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;And so, to configure the parameters of the domain and administrator’s e-mail, as well as the system user name, you need:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select “Domain Settings”.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In field 1, specify the main Domain where your platform is located.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In field 2, the system Email from which notifications will be sent to your clients and users.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In field 2 specify a system username that will also be seen by your clients and users.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;After filling in the fields, be sure to click “Save Changes”.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-06-44.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-06-44.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>System Requirements</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/system_req/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/system_req/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;system-requirements&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  System Requirements&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#system-requirements&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The platform uses PHP language version 8.1 and operating system Ubuntu 20. We would like to note that the php 8.1 version must be installed both for the domain and  for use in the console (via SSH).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The platform requires either a dedicated server or a VPS with root access.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Beforehand, a domain must be connected on the server and an SSL certificate for this domain must be configured.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The operating system used for CMS – Ubuntu 20.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;We recommend the following configuration: 4 GB of RAM, at least 40 GB of hard disk space (preferably SSD), 2+ CORE.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You need to increase PHP max_execution_time in Apache or NGINX and for PHP in CLI mode to 1200&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can install these add-ons yourself, or contact the technical support of your hosting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Required libraries and tools</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/soft_required/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/soft_required/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-required-libraries-and-tools&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Install required libraries and tools&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#install-required-libraries-and-tools&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, update and clean sources list&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go-html-template&#34; data-lang=&#34;go-html-template&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;apt-get update -yqq &lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;  apt-get install -y apt-utils&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;then install this dependencies:&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go-html-template&#34; data-lang=&#34;go-html-template&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;apt-get update &lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; apt-get install -y build-essential libpng-dev  locales zip jpegoptim optipng pngquant gifsicle unzip zip git curl lua-zlib-dev libmemcached-dev wget&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Install NodeJS 22.X&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go-html-template&#34; data-lang=&#34;go-html-template&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x -o setup_22.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sh ./setup_18.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get install -y nodejs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Install NPM&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go-html-template&#34; data-lang=&#34;go-html-template&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://www.npmjs.com/install.sh | sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod +x install.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;./install.sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Install Ionic 7&#xA;Before install Ionic, you must install NPM.&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go-html-template&#34; data-lang=&#34;go-html-template&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm i -g @ionic/cli@7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Users registration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/registration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/registration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;users-registration&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Users registration&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#users-registration&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can change the possibility of registration of new users.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-24-54.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-24-54.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If registration is disabled, new users will not be able to register. However, previously registered users will still be able to operate. Additionally, you can manually add a user.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Installation steps</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/steps/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/steps/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;software-used-and-install-step-by-step&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Software used and Install Step-by-step&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#software-used-and-install-step-by-step&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The following packages must be installed for the platform to work:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Set the domain name to be used for the platform&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Setup domain dir in server&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install an SSL certificate, since the platform only works with a secure connection.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Create MySQL database&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Upload &lt;strong&gt;install.zip&lt;/strong&gt; to domain folder and unpack.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After then, open your domain url in browser and make install with follow the instructions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Trial period</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/trial/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/trial/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;trial-period-settings&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Trial period settings&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#trial-period-settings&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can set the number of trial days for users. After these days expire, billing will start for the user.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;0 - without trial&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-24-54.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-24-54.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Build queue</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/build_queue/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/build_queue/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;user-application-build-queue&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  User application build queue&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#user-application-build-queue&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Applications are added to the queue and then build sequentially, depending on the build mode. If necessary, some applications can be removed from the build queue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Download SDK and Logs</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/dowlload_sdk/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/dowlload_sdk/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;donwload-sdk-and-tools-for-app-build&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Donwload SDK and tools for app build&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#donwload-sdk-and-tools-for-app-build&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Installing the SDKs and tools required to properly generate Android, WWW, IOS, Sources and PWA applications&#xA;some applications can be removed from the build queue.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-44-24.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-44-24.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We recommend installing libraries via NPM – this ensures using the latest versions of these libraries.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The installation process may take some time. To ensure the installation works properly, you need to configure Cron (see Cron setup in the Installation section).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Install Moxly App Builder</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/install_cms/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/install_cms/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;install-moxly-app-builder&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Install Moxly App Builder&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#install-moxly-app-builder&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;steps&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Steps&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#steps&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After install all requred dependencies and tools, you can install platform.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Аollow these steps:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Set the domain name to be used for the platform&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Setup domain dir in server&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install an SSL certificate, since the platform only works with a secure connection.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Create MySQL database&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Upload install.zip to domain folder and unpack.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After then, open your domain url in browser and make install with follow the instructions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Platform updates</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/updates/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/admin_settings/updates/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;license-information&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  License Information&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#license-information&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here you can view your license number and its status, activate or deactivate it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-54-06.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-54-06.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A platform with an inactive license will not receive updates.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;platform-update&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Platform Update&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#platform-update&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In the side menu, go to the “Updates and modules”.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Select a subsection (tab) “Platform update”.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Check for updates by clicking the “Check now” button.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;If there are updates, then click the “Update now” button below.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-56-33.png&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/2025-01-05_13-56-33.png&#34; alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
